{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a7c2d3e4-5f6a-7b8c-9d0e-lamteknik0002",
    "name": "LamTeknik API",
    "description": "Importable Postman collection for API/server-lamteknik.js (default port 4100). All entity routes are templated with the {{entity}} environment variable so the same 8 requests cover every LamTeknik contract.\n\nValid entity slugs (set as `entity` in the env):\nakreditasi, asesmen-kecukupan, asesmen-lapangan, asesor, bank, institusi, jenjang, keputusan-ma, klaster-ilmu, klaster-prodi, klaster-profesi, komite-evaluasi, laporan-asesmen, majelis-akreditasi, pembayaran, penawaran-asesor, pengesahan-ak, pengesahan-al, prodi, provinsi, respon-asesor, sekretariat, tenant, upps, user, validator\n\nUse the `LamTeknik (local)` environment that ships next to this collection. The `privateKey` env var is optional; if left empty the collection's pre-request script strips it from the POST body and the server falls back to DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY / DEFAULT_PRIVATE_KEY in API/.env.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// 1) Re-encode the env `allData` as a JSON-escaped string so the body",
          "//    sends it as a STRING (which is what server-lamteknik.js expects).",
          "//    The env stores plain JSON like {\"id\":42,...}; we wrap it with",
          "//    JSON.stringify so the body literal becomes \"{\\\"id\\\":42,...}\".",
          "const allDataRaw = pm.environment.get('allData') || '';",
          "pm.variables.set('allDataJson', JSON.stringify(allDataRaw));",
          "",
          "// 2) Strip an empty `privateKey` from POST bodies so the server can",
          "//    fall back to its DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY / DEFAULT_PRIVATE_KEY env.",
          "if (pm.request.method === 'POST') {",
          "  const body = pm.request.body;",
          "  const raw = body && body.raw;",
          "  if (raw && /\"privateKey\":\\s*\"\"/.test(raw)) {",
          "    body.raw = raw.replace(/,\\s*\"privateKey\":\\s*\"\"/, '');",
          "  }",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "txHash",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Diagnostics",
      "description": "Server-wide diagnostic endpoints, not tied to any single entity.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Pings the Besu RPC and returns block number + how many LamTeknik contracts the server loaded."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('healthy', () => {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(j.success).to.eql(true);",
                  "  pm.expect(j.status).to.eql('healthy');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /lamteknik (list entities)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/lamteknik",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["lamteknik"]
            },
            "description": "Lists every loaded LamTeknik entity with its slug, contract name, registry key, and on-chain address."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('success', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.eql(true));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /contracts",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/contracts",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["contracts"]
            },
            "description": "Returns a slug -> { contractName, registryKey, address } map for all loaded LamTeknik contracts."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
